Rating: 3
A really nice concept and a fresh take for tuna salad lovers. Maybe a can of tuna could be stretched to serve 3 or 4 in 1956, but today's shrinking size (6 ounces) surely won't. I used two cans of light tuna and two eggs. The seasonings are perfect as is, but the crunchables can be varied. Red bell pepper or diced radishes, for example. Don't be ruled by exact measurements - go with your own sense of proportion on the mayo, etc. I did add a 1/2 tsp of Dijon and chopped parsley. Delicious.

